commitResults.messageTitle: Update ModelManager to have list of CardFolders
Update folder equivalence: see full description
commitResults.messageBody:
Equivalence between folders (between past and present versions of the same folder, between different folders) now checks for identical folderName on top of equivalence between cards. Both conditions need to be true for a folder to equal another.

In the process of making this change, constructors of CardFolder and ModelManager have been modified to require a folderName when creating a new folder from nothing.

The default behaviour of MainApp to instantiate a sample cardfolder has now been removed; if none is read from storage, no cardfolder will be created on instantiation.

Tests have also been heavily modified to reflect the above changes.

commitResults.messageBody: Folder equivalence is determined by folder name. However, when comparing VersionedCardFolders, an additional condition is enforced, where past states need to have the same cards as well on top of having the same name. This is so that VersionedCardFolders will be different if they have different sets of cards in their past states.
